title: The Drill: NFL Week 5 by the numbers
text:
The Drill: NFL Week 5 by the numbers Getty Images Oakland Raiders safety Charles Woodson picks off two passes thrown by Denver quarterback Peyton Manning on Sunday. Oct. 11, 2015 7:58 p.m. NFL WEEK 5 BY THE NUMBERS 
2 Scoring receptions by a Kansas City wide receiver since December 2013. 
3 Points in the first half of the Tennessee-Buffalo game — the fewest of any game this season. 
5 Times New England quarterback Tom Brady was sacked in the first half against Dallas. 
46 Victories by Jay Cutler with the Bears, tying him with Jim McMahon for most wins by a Bears starting QB since the 1970 AFL-NFL merger. 
64 Career interceptions by Charles Woodson, who moved into a tie for sixth with Ed Reed on the all-time list. 
1988 The last year that the Cincinnati Bengals were 5-0 to start the season. 
2012 The last season before Sunday that Detroit quarterback Dan Orlovsky threw a pass in an NFL game. © 2015 , Journal Sentinel Inc. All rights reserved.
